<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-015-316 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 459 040</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Nov 7 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>DAK unveils $1,499 386SX notebook/software bundle. (DAK IndustriesInc.'s BSR 386SX) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Rohrbough, Linda.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   DAK Industries Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   DAK Industries BSR 386SX (Portable computer) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionNotebook computersBundled software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>DAK Unveils $1,499 386SX Notebook/Software Bundle 11/07/91 CANOGA PARK,CALIFORNIA, U.S.A., 1991 NOV 7 (NB) -- Drew A. Kaplin (DAK) Industries, knownfor its mail order electronics business and chatty catalogs written entirelyby the company president, Drew Kaplin, has announced it is offering a BSR386SX notebook computer complete with an impressive bundle of software forjust $1,499.andM;The software includes Microsoft's DOS 5.0, Borland's Paradox 3.5 databaseprogram, the Norton Desktop for Windows utility program, the Maximizer 2.0contact manager program, the Fastlynx file transfer program, the Fastjuicebattery watch program, and EZC Smart Cursor.andP;  The company estimates thissoftware to have a net worth of $1,588.andM;The notebook computer weighs in at 6.8 pounds with batteries, and measures8.5-inches by 11-inches by 2-inches.andP;  It also features an Intel 80386SXcentral processing unit (CPU) running at 16 megahertz (MHz) with a 40MB harddisk, a 3.5-inch disk, a 640 by 480 pixel backlit video graphic array (VGA)screen with 16 gray levels and 1MB of RAM, expandable to 5MB.andP;  Singleparallel and serial ports, along with an external VGA monitor connector plusa keyport port are also included as standard features.andM;Company officials claim that two hours of power is available from the Ni-Cadbatteries.andP;  Alternatively, the notebook can be plugged into a power outletwith the included AC power supply/battery charger.andM;DAK also claims that customers who buy the notebook are also offered theoption of purchasing another collection of software dubbed DAK's ExclusiveSoftware Collection.andM;The additional collection of software includes Windows 3.0, Word for Windows,Adobe Type Manager, Quattro Pro 3.0, Reflex 2.0, Grammatik for Windows,Microsoft Productivity Pack, Sidekick 2.0, GEM Artline, Random HouseEncyclopedia, Ainsworth Keyboard/Keypad Trainer, GEM Graph, Keyform designer,Keyformpac, Wordfinder, Keymailer 2000, PC USA and PC Globe, plus a BSR3-Button mouse.andP;  The software is retail valued by DAK at $3,565, but isoffered to notebook customers for $399.andM;More information is available via a free catalog available by calling800/888-7808 or by writing DAK Industries, 8200 Remmet Avenue, Canoga Park,California, 91304.andM;(Linda Rohrbough/19911107/Press Contact: Bryan Eggers, DAK Industries, Tel:818-716-6219, Fax: 818-348-2642)</TEXT></DOC>